      <section eId="sec_40_5_53">
        <num>40-5-53</num>
        <content>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1937, p. 322, art. 4, § 13; Ga. L. 1939, p. 135, § 12; Ga. L. 1968, p. 430, § 6; Code 1933, § 68B-304, enacted by Ga. L. 1975, p. 1008, § 1; Ga. L. 1985, p. 149, § 40; Ga. L. 1986, p. 1002, § 9; Ga. L. 1987, p. 392, § 1; Ga. L. 1990, p. 1913, § 1; Ga. L. 1990, p. 2048, § 4; Ga. L. 1992, p. 1118, § 1; Ga. L. 1992, p. 2785, § 6; Ga. L. 1993, p. 1665, § 1; Ga. L. 1995, p. 917, § 2; Ga. L. 2000, p. 951, § 5-15; Ga. L. 2003, p. 580, § 1; Ga. L. 2004, p. 471, § 1; Ga. L. 2005, p. 334, § 17-12/HB 501; Ga. L. 2006, p. 449, § 5/HB 1253; Ga. L. 2010, p. 932, § 10/HB 396; Ga. L. 2016, p. 385, § 8/HB 806; Ga. L. 2017, p. 184, § 4/HB 136; Ga. L. 2021, p. 228, § 2/HB 534.)</p>
          <p>The 2016 amendment,
      effective January 1, 2017, designated the existing provisions of subsection (b) as paragraph (b)(1), and added paragraphs (b)(2) through (b)(4).</p>
          <p>The 2017 amendment,
      effective July 1, 2017, deleted "for a violation of Article 7 of this chapter" following "conviction" near the beginning of paragraph (b)(4).</p>
          <p>The 2021 amendment,
      effective May 3, 2021, substituted "40-6-390.1" for "40-6-391" twice in paragraph (b)(3). See Editor's notes for applicability.</p>
